When Yale University social scientists assessed public opinion about climate change last year, they found that 64% of Nebraskans believed climate change was happening.
As such extreme weather events pile up, some say they are beginning to change hearts and minds here – not politically but practically.
“We are not necessarily going around and saying, ‘Hey, climate change, climate change, climate change!” says Mr. Christensen of GC Resolve, who travels the state preaching regenerative agriculture.
Does the extreme weather imply climate change?
